reviews.review_text: Kansas City Dead - Soundboard Ahhh!  Staying inside and practicing social distancing from all this coronavirus.  No better way to spend one's time than sittin' back and groovin' to Jerry, Donna & Keith, & the rest of the good Ol' Boys from a 1977 soundboard.  Thanks for sharing this one!!

Stream As one might expect from Betty's insane record prowess, the music sounds extraordinary, dimensional, and just about perfect. It's taken me a long time to understand my own sonic experience. People like what they like, it's not complicated. Although, many like to over-think what's there and drown their mind with depravity. They choose to focus on what's not there, instead of aLL the majesty this Life can offer to the hopeful and encouraged. You're asking about mine? It's the same as yours, my path is over there, right here, under my feet. I walk with the same tenacity, same vision. Sometimes my eyes are closed, it's more fun. But, I'm never drunk to wise these feelings. Only that I'm hopeful it gets better down the road, but what about choice? Could it not be good now, enough to say the least? Let the words be yours, I am done with mine...
